{"type":"message","id":"89456f71","parentId":"868b7bef","timestamp":"2026-05-15T03:53:32.226Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! I see \"Updating 2946c94..89c735c\" and \"Fast-forward\" with a file change listed. So the git pull actually fetched new changes. And then \"-----Jump out the build step-----\" was logged, followed by a clean shutdown.\n\nSo the pipeline:\n1. Ran Git拉新 - successfully pulled new changes (2946c94..89c735c, with a file change in Effect_510.cs)\n2. Jumped out of the build steps\n3. Shut down cleanly\n\nThe \"Jump out the build step\" could be a normal part of the pipeline flow - perhaps the pipeline configuration has steps that are conditioned or the pipeline only had the git step configured. Or the pipeline jumps out by design after certain conditions are met.\n\nThe return code was 0 (success), so the pipeline executed its configured steps without errors. The key question is whether it did all the steps it was supposed to.\n\nLet me check the bat file to understand what it does, and also check the EditorConfig for the pipeline configuration.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_DHe9R4H6QfyGJbAZWWnv0690","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\RunBuildPipelineHotUpdate.bat"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":509,"output":284,"cacheRead":29952,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30745,"cost":{"input":0.00007126,"output":0.00007952000000000001,"cacheRead":0.000838656,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.000989436}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778817208587,"responseId":"2abea364-b0a3-44dc-b08a-ba23ee1c3a64"}}
