{"type":"message","id":"d408f3dc","parentId":"781da58a","timestamp":"2026-05-15T03:53:41.135Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_xAn3lWSABHIE4YAXuz3n1755","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"                    w.Version = BuildPipelineConfig.APIConfigVersion;\n                    w.Write(BuildPipelineConfig.APIConfigVersion);\n                    w.Write(config);\n                }\n                AssetDatabase.Refresh();\n            }\n        }\n\n        public static void ClearConfig()\n        {\n            config = null;\n        }\n\n        internal static void ExecuteContinued()\n        {\n            SetExecuteState(ExecuteState.Executing);\n            while (!Config.IsExecuteFinished)\n            {\n                if (EditorApplication.isCompiling)\n                {\n                    SaveConfig();\n                    SetExecuteState(ExecuteState.Suspend);\n                    Debug.Log(\"-----Jump out the build step-----\");\n                    return;\n                }\n\n                var lastIndex = Config.ExecuteStack.Count - 1;\n                var step = Config.ExecuteStack[lastIndex];\n                Config.ExecuteStack.RemoveAt(lastIndex);\n                if (step != null)\n                {\n                    using (new LogStamp(\"Excute Pipline:\" + step.Name))\n                    {\n                        if (!ExecuteStep(step))\n                        {\n                            SetExecuteState(ExecuteState.Canceled);\n                            TryBatchExitNowIfDone();\n                            return;\n                        }\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n            SetExecuteState(ExecuteState.Succeeded);\n            TryBatchExitNowIfDone();\n        }\n\n        internal static bool ExecuteStep(BuildPipelineStep step)\n        {\n            try\n            {\n                IsBuilding = true;\n                if (step.IsBuildActionValid)\n                {\n                    step.BuildAction?.Invoke();\n                }\n            }\n            catch (Exception e)\n            {\n                throw;\n            }\n            finally\n            {\n                IsBuilding = false;\n            }\n\n            return true;\n        }\n\n        internal static void ExecuteSelected(BuildPipelineLine line)\n        {\n            Config.ExecuteStack.Clear();\n            ExecutePipeline(line, true);\n        }\n\n        internal static void Execute(BuildPipelineLine line)\n        {\n            Config.ExecuteStack.Clear();\n            ExecutePipeline(line, false);\n        }\n\n        internal static bool IsDone()\n        {\n            return executeState == ExecuteState.Succeeded || executeState == ExecuteState.Canceled;\n        }\n\n        internal static bool LastRunSucceeded => executeState == ExecuteState.Succeeded;\n\n        private static void ExecutePipeline(BuildPipelineLine line, bool selectedOnly)\n        {\n            if (line != null)\n            {\n                if (Config.ExecuteStack.Count > 0)\n                {\n                    Config.ExecuteStack.RemoveAt(Config.ExecuteStack.Count - 1);\n                }\n\n                //嵌套执行\n                for (int i = line.Steps.Count - 1; i >= 0; --i)\n                {\n                    var step = line.Steps[i];\n                    if (step.IsBuildActionValid && (!selectedOnly || step.Selected))\n                    {\n                        Config.ExecuteStack.Add(step);\n                    }\n                }\n                ExecuteContinued();\n            }\n        }\n\n        private static void SetExecuteState(ExecuteState executeState)\n        {\n            BuildPipeline.executeState = executeState;\n            EditorPrefs.SetInt(ExecuteVariable, (int)executeState);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1778817221135}}
{"type":"message","id":"a65fd4da","parentId":"d408f3dc","timestamp":"2026-05-15T03:53:51.460Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand! The \"-----Jump out the build step-----\" message is logged when `EditorApplication.isCompiling` is true. This means that during the pipeline execution, Unity started compiling scripts (probably because the git pull brought in new/changed files that triggered a recompile).\n\nLooking at the git pull output:\n```\nUpdating 2946c94..89c735c\nFast-forward\n Battle1V1/BattleBuff/Effect/Effect_510.cs     | 41 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++\n```\n\nSo the git pull updated a `.cs` file (Effect_510.cs), which triggered a script recompile. When the pipeline tried to proceed to the next step, it detected `EditorApplication.isCompiling == true` and jumped out.\n\nThis means:\n1. ✅ Git拉新 - DONE, pulled new changes\n2. ❌ 打包资源 + 上传CDN - SKIPPED due to compilation being in progress\n\nHowever, the Unity Editor exited with return code 0 (success), which suggests this is handled as a success case, not an error. But the build steps were skipped.\n\nThe question is: does the pipeline need to be run again to complete the remaining steps? Let me check if there's a way to see if subsequent steps were also configured.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the code flow:\n\n1. `ExecutePipeline` pushes all valid steps onto the stack\n2. `ExecuteContinued` processes them one by one\n3. After the \"Git拉新\" step executes, it falls back into the while loop\n4. At that point, `EditorApplication.isCompiling` is true (because the git pull changed a .cs file)\n5. So it logs \"Jump out the build step\", saves config, and returns\n6. Then `TryBatchExitNowIfDone()` is called, and since the executeState is still `Suspend` (not \"Succeeded\" or \"Canceled\"), `IsDone()` returns false... wait let me re-read.\n\nActually, looking at the code:\n```csharp\ninternal static void ExecuteContinued()\n{\n    SetExecuteState(ExecuteState.Executing);\n    while (!Config.IsExecuteFinished)\n    {\n        if (EditorApplication.isCompiling)\n        {\n            SaveConfig();\n            SetExecuteState(ExecuteState.Suspend);\n            Debug.Log(\"-----Jump out the build step-----\");\n            return;\n        }\n        ...\n    }\n    SetExecuteState(ExecuteState.Succeeded);\n    TryBatchExitNowIfDone();\n}\n```\n\nWhen the pipeline jumps out, it sets `ExecuteState.Suspend`, not `Succeeded`. So `IsDone()` returns false.\n\nThen `TryBatchExitNowIfDone()` is called:\n```csharp\nprivate static void TryBatchExitNowIfDone()\n{\n    if (!EditorPrefs.GetBool(BatchExitAfterDonePrefKey, false))\n        return;\n    if (!IsDone())\n        return;\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nSince `IsDone()` returns false, `TryBatchExitNowIfDone()` just returns without exiting. So technically the editor should NOT have exited...\n\nWait, but the `ExecuteContinued` function is called from within the while loop in `BeginBatchCli`. Let me re-read:\n\n```csharp\nprivate static void BeginBatchCli(string pipeline, bool selectedOnly)\n{\n    ...\n    try\n    {\n        Config.ExecuteStack.Clear();\n        ExecutePipeline(pipe, selectedOnly);\n    }\n    catch (Exception e)\n    {\n        Debug.LogException(e);\n        ClearBatchExitRequest();\n        EditorApplication.Exit(1);\n        return;\n    }\n    TryBatchExitNowIfDone();\n}\n```\n\nAnd `ExecutePipeline`:\n```csharp\nprivate static void ExecutePipeline(BuildPipelineLine line, bool selectedOnly)\n{\n    ...\n    ExecuteContinued();\n}\n```\n\nSo the flow is:\n1. `BeginBatchCli` → `ExecutePipeline` → `ExecuteContinued`\n2. `ExecuteContinued` processes the \"Git拉新\" step, falls back to the while loop\n3. Detects compiling → saves config, sets state to Suspend, logs message, returns\n4. Back in `ExecutePipeline`, returns from `ExecuteContinued()`, returns from `ExecutePipeline`\n5. Back in `BeginBatchCli`, calls `TryBatchExitNowIfDone()`\n6. Since IsDone() returns false (state is Suspend), TryBatchExitNowIfDone just returns\n7. BeginBatchCli returns\n8. Back in `RunHotUpdatePipeline`, the method returns\n9. Unity's -quit flag causes it to exit\n\nBut the bat output says \"Exiting batchmode successfully now!\" which indicates the pipeline ran but jumped out.\n\nHmm, so the pipeline partially ran - only the first step \"Git拉新\" executed, then compilation triggered a suspension. The remaining steps (打包资源, 上传CDN, etc.) were skipped.\n\nActually wait - let me look again at the specific pipeline configuration to understand what steps it has.\n\nLet me check the config file that stores the pipeline definition.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"流水线因 Git 拉新导致文件变化触发重新编译而跳过后续步骤。让我检查完整执行状态。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_0peeIFB4XGjkkQfUthIG1895","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Content \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log\" | Select-String \"Jump out\" -Context 5,5","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":678,"output":1164,"cacheRead":32768,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34610,"cost":{"input":0.00009492,"output":0.00032592,"cacheRead":0.000917504,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001338344}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778817221136,"responseId":"921bd392-58ca-448b-b3e1-486b18d8d4f5"}}
