{"type":"message","id":"86c5a493","parentId":"18d9bf3b","timestamp":"2026-05-15T03:53:58.171Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay, so the execution was jumped out because the compilation started. This is because the git pull brought in changes to `Effect_510.cs`, which triggered a script recompilation. The pipeline was interrupted at this point.\n\nSince the build steps (打包资源, 上传CDN) were not executed, the test server hasn't been fully updated. I need to run the pipeline again after the compilation finishes.\n\nBut wait - the Unity process has already exited. So the compilation was not completed, and the script compilation state is still pending. To properly finish the pipeline, we need to run it again.\n\nHowever, there's a complication: the Git拉新 step already ran successfully and pulled the latest code. If I run the pipeline again, the git pull step will say \"Already up to date\" and won't trigger a recompilation, allowing the remaining steps to proceed.\n\nLet me think about this more carefully. The git pull updated a .cs file, but the player in Unity has already unloaded. So when I re-run the pipeline:\n1. Git拉新 will run again - it will say \"Already up to date\" (no new changes to pull)\n2. The remaining steps should proceed without compilation interruption\n\nBut actually, the compilation might still happen because the project just underwent a reimport. The .asset file imports happened while Unity was running. Let me just try running the pipeline again.\n\nActually, let me also check if there's been a git status issue. The pipeline's git pull step pulled new changes (2946c94..89c735c), including Effect_510.cs. Now the local repo is up to date. If I run the pipeline again, the git pull will be a no-op, and the remaining steps should proceed.\n\nLet me run the pipeline again to complete the remaining steps.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Git 更新了 .cs 文件触发了编译，流水线中断了后续打包/上传步骤。需要重新运行流水线来完成剩